            "autoAdvance": true,
            "narration": {
                "id": "gui.tutorials.jsForOfLoop.intro",
                "default": "In Scratch you walk a list by writing a repeat plus item-i-of-list. JavaScript has a shortcut called the for-of loop. It hands you each item one by one, no index counter needed. When you only need the items themselves, this is the cleanest loop."
